Well back when you could still do a &quot;/who count all&quot; at peak times there were around 3000.  Most peopel figured that was about half of the total people that played on the Rathe.  Hard to know how many now, but probably at least 8000 or more.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 2. How many of those people are planable?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Would be interesting to know.  I think most people would agree at least 75%.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 3. How many planable guilds are there?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
36<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 4. How many planable people/guilds run the RTA board?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Currently BotS,  and Noble Blade, have RTA admins.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 5. Do we even like the people who run the RTA?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Some people I am sure do, and I am sure many don't.  Find a single person that everyone likes that will run this message board and admin the calendar/rotation systems.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 6. Why do we need the, sorry to say, dictator guilds telling everyone else where they can hunt and when? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
hmm haven't seen this.  BotS doesn't tell my guild where/when we can hunt.  In fact no other guild has either, nor we would allow one.  Guilds have agreed to follow certain process for certain zones/npcs.  That is why we have the rotation system for npcs,  and why we have the planes calendar.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 7. Why do we allow these people to tell us when we can camp ragefire?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Any cleric that wants to camp ragefire can.  However The guilds on the server have agreed that a cleric should only need the ragefire drop to complete epic before camping ragefire.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 8. Why is it ragefire is not allowed to be camped by anyone under lvl 56?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
A cleric under level 56 can camp ragefire.  I know of of no such rule for this. I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> think</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the epic is only useable to 51+, might be wrong not for sure. So really doesn't make sense for a cleric under 51 then to camp ragefire.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 9. Is Rathe so an@l retentive that we tell clerics &quot;don't do your epic cause your not ALLOWED to get it until lvl 56, because RTA says so?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
See above, not for sure where you are getting this information. Maybe you shoudl read the Rathe Etiquette Forum<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 10. WHY!!!! are the people who run RTA telling the server how and when to play?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
They don't.  The Planes Calendar was a system discussed over several months about 2 years ago, by all the guilds of the server.  It was an agreed upon method.  Rotation systems were agreed upon by guilds that coudl kill the NPC.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 11. Is the Rathe made up of a bunch of children who need direction and guidance from other children?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well at one point in time before we tried to become a civil server  it very well may have appeared this way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 12. Why do we have a rotation calendar? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Have you been part of group going after a race npc?  Take Venril Sathir for instance.  Have you been part of a group going to kill him when there is a second group going for him?  Imagine 2 guilds running through Karnors Castle trying to get him.  It can be chaotic, lots of deaths,  flames erupt that make Talendor's breath seem like a cold december wind, and that is if it doesn't go to badly.  So those guilds that could kill an NPC that was highly desired like Tormax,  Dozekar, NTOV, and such agreed to rotate the NPC instead of racing each other for it, and creating problems.  SIDE NOTE:  Sounds very grown upish if you ask me,  see question 11.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 13. Why do we have to sign up and why are there rules?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Simply put 2 years ago this server got tired of the flames, fights, training, name calling, and not getting to see things, that they created the Rathe Travel Agency here to discuss Rathe Server issues.  Guilds sent representatives here to speak on behalf of their guild.  What was created was the Rathe Planes Calendar. This allowed many guild to go the planes alone, where they could have the entire planes to themselves.  Instead of the previous of having 2-3 guilds in the planes generally making each other miserable.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 14. Why do I need permission to go to the planes?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Simply put you do not.  The Planes Calendar is a Reservation system. It simply states that Guild/Alliance  X  has reserved Plane Y  on day Z, and all other guilds/alliances on the Planes Calendar respects Guild/Alliance X claim to the planes day Z.  Anyone can enter the planes on a day that is not reserved.  However entering the Planes on a day that is reserved and it is not your reservation, is well very bad form.  The Repurcussiosn are many guilds would be less likely to help you on a wipeout, or in the future when you have other problem.  Remeber your reputation is what you carry forward. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 15. What are the GM's/Verant views to my guild going to the planes while not on the RTA board?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Don't know their official view on the RTA.  However keep in mind that the RTA is what 95%+ of the other playes on the server have agreed to.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 16. How is it that you all fight about RF all the time but no one has the balls to say screw the RTA my guild will take it down if we engage first. Then to have whining little babies come running to the RTA/Flame board, just so they can bash someone for playing the game by the game rules?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Respect for other playes.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 17. Why is my guild not allowed to bring more then 6 people from another posting entity guild to my raid?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well for planes raids this was one of the agreed upon rules by all the Guild Leaders/Representatives when the Planes calendar was decided upon.  The rule no more than 6 from the same posting entity that is not your enitity.  This is to prevent double dipping.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 18. Who makes up all these rules?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The Guild Leaders/Representatives and the guilds on the rotation for a particular npc.  Clerics to an extent have defined the Ragefire Rules.  The rules are made by those it effects.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 19. So can I make an RTA board add a Flame central then start spouting rules and you will all follow them?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Can you get 95% of the server to agree to your rules?  If so then the answer is yes.  If the answer is no then probably not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 20. So is the RTA a majority or is it a handful of people telling a few thousand what to do?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Majority of the players on the Rathe are in a guild.  Majority of the decisions are made by their Guild Leaders/Representatives.  <br>
<br>
<br>
